            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-03-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="540"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                <head>540. Telegram 1474 from The Hague<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d540fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/3–1656. Confidential.
                        Repeated for information to Geneva as telegram 17 and to Taipei as telegram
                        1.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>The Hague</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1956-03-16">March 16, 1956, 6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d540-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d540-1"/>
                <p>1474. Foreign Office official has informed Embassy representative that Chiao
                    Kwang-hua, Chinese Communist Deputy Minister Foreign Affairs, discussed with
                    Zeeman, Netherlands Charge Peking March 4 communique which Chinese Communists
                    issued re Geneva talks. Chiao pointed out that, although communique threatened
                    US with rupture talks unless either October 27 or December 1 proposals accepted,
                    Chinese Communists had deliberately fixed no time limit for such acceptance.</p>
                <p>Zeeman reported that he feels this observation was made to him for specific
                    purpose of relay to US Government. It was his impression that Chinese Communists
                    were willing, despite tenor of communique, to continue talks in Geneva.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Matthews</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
